ce:section.ce:para:
The assembly stage can lead to an internal short circuit in several ways. The most common way is probably the introduction of metal particles. It can occur from several sources.

                                    -

During cutting as well as during welding, particles coming from the electrode (Cu and Al particles from foils and active material dusts) may be produced [74];


                                    -

Cutting can result in burrs on electrode edges [74];


                                    -

Particles attached to the metallic parts, such as current collectors, cans and covers, may be released and deposit on the electrodes;


                                    -

Improperly cleaned tools or non-clean manufacturing environment might be a source of undesired particles.
